## Overview  
**Dr. Greg Carr** is a leading scholar, historian, and educator in the field of Africana Studies. He serves as an Associate Professor of Africana Studies at **Howard University**, where he is also the former Chair of the Department of Afro-American Studies. Dr. Carr is widely known for his expertise in African history, Black political thought, and his advocacy for African-centered education and liberation.

