## Timeline  

- **1990s (20th Century):** Earned his J.D. from The Ohio State University and Ph.D. in Africana Studies from Temple University.  
- **2009 (21st Century):** Appointed Chair of Afro-American Studies at Howard University.  
- **2015 (21st Century):** Co-founded the Howard University Graduate Africana Studies Initiative.  
- **2020 (21st Century):** Became a prominent voice in public discourse on African American history and cultural identity.  

